A '''stochastic decision chip''' was a type of experimental [[Droid/Legends|droid]] processor developed during the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Old Republic]]. This module allowed a droid to make random decisions about given situations for a time, allowing itself to learn the best course of action in each situation. Stochastic chip were used by Republic forces by the time of the [[Invasion of Naboo/Legends|Battle of Naboo]] but most of the droids equipped with such chips were later destroyed. During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], the only remaining chip was contained by a [[B2-series super battle droid/Legends|B2 super battle droid]] taken on [[Naboo/Legends|Naboo]] by the [[Ultragungans|Ultragungan Militia]] as a spoil of war.<ref name="SWG:ORDMTGBD">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=class|Legacy|Old Republic Droid Modules: The Gungan Battle Droid|Naboo}}</ref> In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]],<ref name="SWG_timeline">{{SWG_timeline}}</ref> a spacer managed to access to the droid thanks to the help of [[Boss/Legends|Boss]] [[Rugor Nass/Legends|Nass]] and destroyed it to recover the stochastic decision chip.<ref name="SWG:ORDMTGBD" />

